---
title: Hoisin Duck Stir-Fry with Egg Noodles and Red Pepper
description: Fresh, flavoursome and easy to cook, the reasons why we love this 30-minute hoisin duck stir-fry are endless. In this recipe, we’ve used pre-cooked duck confit legs to help you get full on flavour in double quick time - simply shred the meat and add it straight to your veg-filled frying pan. Finish by coating everything with the glossy hoisin sauce and serve piping hot with a sprinkling of fresh coriander. Delicious!
